Class LoggerSlf4j

java.lang.Object
org.slf4j.helpers.AbstractLogger
com.dua3.utility.logging.backend.slf4j.LoggerSlf4j
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, org.slf4j.Logger
public class LoggerSlf4j extends org.slf4j.helpers.AbstractLogger
This class represents a logger implementation using the SLF4J logging framework. It extends the AbstractLogger class.

It is used to forward SLF4J log messages to applications.

Note that SLF4J markers are not supported by this implementation, i.e., markers in logging calls are ignored and logging is done as though the marker was not present.

    • isEnabled

      public boolean isEnabled(org.slf4j.event.Level level)
      Determines if the specified logging level is enabled for this logger. The method compares the logger's current level with the provided level, returning true if the current level is less than or equal to the specified level.
      Parameters:
      level - the logging level to check
      Returns:
      true if the provided logging level is enabled, false otherwise

    • isEnabled

      public boolean isEnabled(@Nullable org.slf4j.Marker marker, org.slf4j.event.Level level)
      Determines whether logging is enabled for the specified level and marker.

      Note that SLF4J markers are ignored by this implementation.

      Parameters:
      marker - the marker to filter log messages; may be null to indicate no filtering based on markers
      level - the logging level to check against
      Returns:
      true if the current logging level is less than or equal to the specified level, false otherwise
